i cant seem to feel any better i am weeks pergnant w twins i cant seem to get passed the nausea and vomiting i feel like i have the flu all day long please any suggestions on how to feel a little better will help first of all congratulations on twins is this your first pregnancy i am weeks along and expecting my first around christmas time unfortunately morning sickness is sometimes part of the baby bargain i had severe morning sickness up until weeks i was advised it would last until weeks and soon found out that some women get morning sickness right til bubs is born what i found helpful is eating something dry in the mornings i used to have crackers on my bedside table or get my partner to run and grab me some toast then i'd avoid the kitchen as i felt the smells from there werent helping the best thing i can recommend is try the dry foods before you get up method also ginger crystals or ginger beer is handy but if none of that works you'd be best to see your doctor as sometimes they can prescribe you something for it all the best and good luck Morning sickness Ginger Pregnancy Stomach cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Obstetrics Breastfeeding Hyperemesis gravidarum Vomiting Prostate cancer Common cold Adjustable gastric band Gastroparesis Psoriasis Breech birth Cuisine of Denmark Fecal incontinence Hypoglycemia Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Charles Darwin's illness Fasting Urinary incontinence Chronic fatigue syndrome Emergency contraception Tofu Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban M__ni__re___s disease Childbirth Anorexia nervosa Gonorrhoea Twin Dehydration Social rule Miscarriage Japanese cuisine Abortion Folic acid Word of Wisdom Chinese New Year Fertility awareness Medical cannabis Rule of St Benedict Motion sickness Binge eating disorder Medical prescription Spanish flu Avenue Q Paracetamol Clinical depression H5N1 Sexual abstinence Knots Landing Coeliac disease Diarrhea Prolactinoma Mojave people Chicken 